description.plain:
Eric Allen (b. June 20th, 2002) better known by his stage name, Lil Eazzyy is a recording artist from Chicago, Illinois that first blew up with his single Onna Come Up off of his debut EP, Underrated.

Following the success of the single, Allen would be signed to Atlantic Records and a remix featuring G Herbo was released in early 2021.

Allen would release his debut project under Atlantic, Rookie Of The Year which would bolster fourteen songs and feature Tay Keith and Bizzy Banks.

His second project under Atlantic, titled Too Eazzyy was released in 2022 and would feature NLE Choppa.

description.plain:
“Onna Come Up” is Lil Eazzyy’s best performing single to date, racking up over ten million views during the latter half of 2020.

Ironically, the rapper started generating major buzz online because of this very song.
